# Project Rules (Always Apply)

- Stack: Next.js App Router (app/), TypeScript, Tailwind, shadcn/ui.
- Hosting: Vercel. Assume serverless/stateless; no runtime filesystem writes.
- Components: Server Components by default. Add "use client" only when necessary.
- Blog: Sanity is the source of truth. Never expose Sanity write tokens to the client.
- Forms: Validate server-side; implement basic spam protection patterns.
- Dependencies: Do not add new dependencies without explaining why and alternatives.
- Quality: Keep changes PR-sized. Run lint + typecheck after edits and fix issues.
